details.purpose: To record details about health education material provided to the subject.
details.use: Use to record details about health education intervention, such as advice or physical material, provided to the subject, including links to the information itself. For example, a record of fact sheets provided to the patient about the risks of a vasectomy.
details.misuse: Not to be used to record consent - for example consent to a vasectomy after provision of a fact sheet about vasectomy.

items.items: Health education information provided or imparted to the subject.
Topic of health education information provided.
Narrative description of the health education information provided.
Method by which the health education information was provided.

For example, verbal or written. This is not the same as participation. Material can be exchanged between an educator and a subject in various ways during a face-to-face consultation or via teleconference. In specific situations it may be important to document that writtern fact sheets have been physically handed to the subject, for example regarding the risks of vasectomy.
Internet link to the information provided.
For example: reason why the information exchange is planned; or why the exchange was not successful.
Title or identifier of health education information provided.
All planned activities for education have been successfully completed.
Planned education postponed prior to commencement.
Planned education was cancelled prior to commencement.
Education session was abandoned before complete.
Planned education sessions were suspended after commencement.
Subjective, narrative assessment of outcome of the health education intervention.
For example: a narrative description about patient understanding.
Number of the education session in an multi-session course.
